Here is the commit message:
Restrict HTTP methods on Servlet HiddenHttpMethodFilter

This commit restricts the allowed HTTP methods on HiddenHttpMethodFilter
(Servlet variant) to the following: PUT, DELETE, PATCH.

This filter is meant to be used to simulate those methods from HTML
forms sent by browsers, so no other methods are allowed.

Issue: SPR-16836
(Cherry-picked from f64fa3dea1)

Here is the root cause:
The `HiddenHttpMethodFilter` was allowing HTTP methods beyond the intended scope, which could lead to unexpected behavior when processing requests. The filter was designed to simulate PUT, DELETE, and PATCH methods from HTML forms, but it did not restrict other methods, potentially causing security and functionality issues.

Here is the patch:
